    <stitle>CE 200, CE 300 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - Install - Head Lamp</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Head Lamp</title>
        <para>When installing new halogen head lamp bulbs, it is recommended to follow the bulb manufacturer's
            instructions for proper handling of the halogen bulb.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert halogen bulb in socket assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install seal as needed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place bulb and connector in headlight housing receptacle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Twist retainer to lock in place.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install socket cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If no other bulbs are to be replaced, close hood and secure hood latches.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
